  <description>This is Persian recipies</description>
  <recipes>
    <recipe>
      <id>Top1</id>
      <title>Qorme Sabzi(stew)</title>
      <date>2019-03-13</date>
      <ingredients>
        <ingredient>
          <name>mixed persian vegtables (parsley,coriander,fungreek,persian leek,spinach)</name>
          <amount>400</amount>
          <unit>grams</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>lamb diced</name>
          <amount>300</amount>
          <unit>grams</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>onion</name>
          <amount>1</amount>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>red beens</name>
          <amount>200</amount>
          <unit>grams</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>dried lime</name>
          <amount>3</amount>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>turmeric</name>
          <amount>1.5</amount>
          <unit>tea spoon</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>salt</name>
          <amount>2</amount>
          <unit>tea spoon</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>water</name>
          <amount>2</amount>
          <unit>cups</unit>
        </ingredient>
        <ingredient>
          <name>rice</name>
          <amount>3</amount>
          <unit>cups</unit>
        </ingredient>
      </ingredients>
      <preparationSteps>
        <step>Dice onion and put it in hot extra olive oil until it gets a caramelise colour</step>
        <step>Add turmaric to them</step>
        <step>Add meat and red beens to the onions</step>
        <step>Add water to the ingredients and let them boil slowly for 1.5 hours</step>
        <step>Add vegtables,dried limes, salt to your dish</step>
        <step>Let all ingredients boil for another 1 hour </step>
        <step>Make the rice as usuall. When the stew is ready you can have it with the rice and 
             have some persian salad or yoghurt beside your "Qorme Sabzi"</step>
      </preparationSteps>
      <comment>Qorme Sabzi is one of the most delisious Persian foods that everyone should try it</comment>
      <nutritions>
        <nutrition>
          <calories>400</calories>
          <fat>23</fat>
          <protein>50</protein>
        </nutrition>
      </nutritions>
      <related ref="qurme sabzi">this goes very well with persian salad or yoghurt</related>
    </recipe>
